THE BAGGAGE-TRAIN.-The heavy baggage (impedimenta) of the legion was carried by pack animals (jumenta), horses or mules. Wagons or carts, while occasionally used by the army, were more generally found only with the sutlers (mercatores), who followed the legions. The light baggage (sarcinae) was carried by the soldiers.
